1
00:00:05,940 --> 00:00:08,507
♫ I want to go to the future ♫

2
00:00:08,507 --> 00:00:12,162
♫  Time bears witness to my quirkiness  ♫

3
00:00:12,162 --> 00:00:18,190
♫ I want to seize the day and put the whole world into my head ♫

4
00:00:18,190 --> 00:00:24,381
♫ I want to go back in time to do all the crazy things I didn't do ♫

5
00:00:24,381 --> 00:00:30,702
♫  Don't say goodbye, don't be in a daze, let my radiant light be bright  ♫

6
00:00:30,702 --> 00:00:35,988
♫ We are always looking forward to the unknown future ♫

7
00:00:35,988 --> 00:00:43,188
♫  And often overlooking our surroundings and best plan in front of us  ♫

8
00:00:43,188 --> 00:00:48,312
♫ Every day my heart beats for you ♫

9
00:00:48,312 --> 00:00:49,925
♫ Be your light ♫

10
00:00:49,925 --> 00:00:55,588
♫  You are no doubt irreplaceable  ♫

11
00:00:55,588 --> 00:01:02,088
♫ Every day the sun shines through the window ♫

12
00:01:02,088 --> 00:01:07,955
♫ With the reflection of you being my incredible highlight ♫

13
00:01:07,955 --> 00:01:11,602
[I Don't Want to be Brothers with You]

14
00:01:12,900 --> 00:01:15,719
Run! Keep running!

15
00:01:15,719 --> 00:01:17,779
How will you escape?

16
00:01:18,879 --> 00:01:20,696
You're still running?

17
00:01:22,770 --> 00:01:24,699
You're still running?

18
00:01:24,699 --> 00:01:26,398
You're still running?

19
00:01:27,380 --> 00:01:29,000
You ran away for a dozen years!

20
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:32,020
Are you still going to be a coward?

21
00:01:39,100 --> 00:01:41,319
You already ran away once.

22
00:01:41,319 --> 00:01:43,120
You're going to run again?

23
00:01:43,120 --> 00:01:45,319
Aren't you ashamed of yourself?

24
00:01:47,760 --> 00:01:50,040
You just abandoned that child back then.

25
00:01:50,040 --> 00:01:52,280
Are you worthy of being a father?

26
00:02:01,640 --> 00:02:03,682
I'm not worthy!

27
00:02:03,682 --> 00:02:06,319
I'm a bad person!

28
00:02:06,319 --> 00:02:09,320
Why don't you go home and apologize?

29
00:02:09,320 --> 00:02:10,870
Apologize?

30
00:02:11,870 --> 00:02:13,376
Apologize?

31
00:02:20,939 --> 00:02:22,720
Do I still have a chance?

32
00:02:24,919 --> 00:02:26,639
Will you forgive me?

33
00:02:30,759 --> 00:02:33,420
Do you know how much your child misses you?

34
00:02:33,420 --> 00:02:36,039
For so many years, she just wanted to see you.

35
00:02:36,420 --> 00:02:38,719
Can't you at least do that?

36
00:02:39,219 --> 00:02:40,884
Really?

37
00:02:47,090 --> 00:02:48,716
My child,

38
00:02:50,240 --> 00:02:52,600
I'm so sorry.

39
00:02:54,773 --> 00:02:57,700
You have to go home and tell them.

40
00:03:07,779 --> 00:03:09,980
- How do you have to audacity to come back?
- Auntie, Auntie!

41
00:03:09,980 --> 00:03:11,439
Don't stop me! He deserves a beating!

42
00:03:11,439 --> 00:03:12,379
Auntie!

43
00:03:12,379 --> 00:03:15,460
Don't stop her! Let her beat me up.

44
00:03:16,080 --> 00:03:17,744
I deserve it.

45
00:03:18,240 --> 00:03:20,779
I... I was wrong.

46
00:03:20,779 --> 00:03:23,119
What did you do wrong? Tell me!

47
00:03:24,140 --> 00:03:25,882
For so many years,

48
00:03:28,479 --> 00:03:30,880
I've been eaten away by guilt.

49
00:03:30,880 --> 00:03:33,740
I regret abandoning my child.

50
00:03:34,759 --> 00:03:36,700
But at the time,

51
00:03:36,700 --> 00:03:39,420
I really owed a lot of debt!

52
00:03:39,420 --> 00:03:41,439
If I bring the child along, how will she survive?

53
00:03:41,439 --> 00:03:43,699
How will she survive?

54
00:03:44,560 --> 00:03:46,099
I was wrong!

55
00:03:46,099 --> 00:03:47,539
I'm a bad person!

56
00:03:47,539 --> 00:03:49,779
I'm a bad person! I'm a bad person!

57
00:03:49,779 --> 00:03:52,239
I'm a bad person! I'm a bad person!

58
00:03:52,239 --> 00:03:52,939
I...

59
00:03:52,939 --> 00:03:54,120
Don't do that.

60
00:03:54,120 --> 00:03:55,939
What did you say downstairs? Hurry up.

61
00:03:55,939 --> 00:03:57,439
Son,

62
00:03:57,439 --> 00:03:59,780
please... please forgive me.

63
00:03:59,780 --> 00:04:02,659
Wait a minute. This is my son.

64
00:04:02,659 --> 00:04:06,420
Brother, he will always be your son.

65
00:04:06,420 --> 00:04:10,220
I can never repay you for raising him up over the years!

66
00:04:10,220 --> 00:04:11,659
I'll kneel in front of you, Brother!

67
00:04:11,659 --> 00:04:13,319
- No!
- Thank you.

68
00:04:13,319 --> 00:04:16,780
You've made a mistake. This is my biological son. Biological...

69
00:04:18,099 --> 00:04:19,639
Biological son.

70
00:04:19,639 --> 00:04:21,859
That's right. I'm his biological son.

71
00:04:23,759 --> 00:04:25,339
You've made a mistake.

72
00:04:28,659 --> 00:04:30,539
Son,

73
00:04:30,539 --> 00:04:32,720
I'm so sorry!

74
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:36,300
Wait, Mi Daqiang, what's wrong with you? Sit down!

75
00:04:36,300 --> 00:04:37,899
Go back to your seat!

76
00:04:39,779 --> 00:04:40,600
Son...

77
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:44,260
Let me tell you, this is your daughter!

78
00:04:44,260 --> 00:04:48,599
This one and this one have nothing to do with you! Do you hear me?

79
00:04:48,599 --> 00:04:49,900
Not related.

80
00:04:49,900 --> 00:04:52,460
What's going on here?

81
00:04:55,920 --> 00:04:57,845
They are not mine?

82
00:04:57,845 --> 00:05:01,877
Dad, i-it's me.

83
00:05:12,061 --> 00:05:14,086
But I abandoned a boy.

84
00:05:14,086 --> 00:05:15,759
Mi Daqiang, we've come this far.

85
00:05:15,759 --> 00:05:17,959
Don't start with that son preference thing.

86
00:05:17,959 --> 00:05:20,199
But I did abandon a boy!

87
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:28,894
Wait, that's not possible.

88
00:05:28,894 --> 00:05:32,180
The time, location, and surname match up.

89
00:05:32,180 --> 00:05:34,219
How... How could there be such a coincidence?

90
00:05:34,219 --> 00:05:37,040
I'm telling you, Mi Daqiang, don't... don't joke with me.

91
00:05:37,040 --> 00:05:39,079
Why would I make a joke now?

92
00:05:39,079 --> 00:05:40,800
Mi Daqiang,

93
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:45,060
are you sure you abandoned a boy at the time?

94
00:05:45,060 --> 00:05:48,939
I know the gender of my own child! It was a boy.

95
00:05:48,939 --> 00:05:51,300
I'm sure it was a boy.

96
00:05:55,166 --> 00:05:59,679
S-So, you're not my dad?

97
00:06:02,439 --> 00:06:04,239
Auntie...

98
00:06:04,779 --> 00:06:07,819
isn't my Auntie?

99
00:06:07,819 --> 00:06:11,359
Auntie, Mi Jia, this is my fault. I was responsible.

100
00:06:11,359 --> 00:06:12,759
I... I was so unreliable.

101
00:06:12,759 --> 00:06:15,079
I was in such a rush to get her here without confirming the truth!

102
00:06:15,079 --> 00:06:19,939
I'm so sorry! It's my fault. It's all my fault! I'm sorry.

103
00:06:19,939 --> 00:06:22,400
Where did your child go?

104
00:06:22,400 --> 00:06:24,720
He's still suffering out there.

105
00:06:24,720 --> 00:06:26,759
It's all your fault, Mi Daqiang!

106
00:06:26,759 --> 00:06:28,519
- Don't... don't do that!
- You abandoned that child!

107
00:06:28,519 --> 00:06:30,720
He's still suffering out there!

108
00:06:30,720 --> 00:06:33,160
- Sister!
- It's all your fault!

109
00:06:33,160 --> 00:06:34,079
Don't stop me!

110
00:06:34,079 --> 00:06:35,600
He deserves a beating, you know?

111
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:37,399
I was wrong!

112
00:06:37,399 --> 00:06:40,299
There's no use beating him up.

113
00:06:40,299 --> 00:06:41,975
Let her do it! Don't stop her!

114
00:06:41,975 --> 00:06:43,319
It's all your fault!

115
00:06:43,319 --> 00:06:44,160
Mi Jia.

116
00:06:44,160 --> 00:06:45,759
It was my fault.

117
00:06:45,759 --> 00:06:48,260
Jia'er, I didn't mean that!

118
00:06:48,260 --> 00:06:50,320
Auntie, Auntie!

119
00:06:50,320 --> 00:06:52,480
Let them comfort her first.

120
00:06:58,120 --> 00:07:00,740
Where is she? Which way did she go?

121
00:07:27,319 --> 00:07:29,820
I'm still an orphan.

122
00:07:29,820 --> 00:07:33,940
I... I have no parents.

123
00:07:33,940 --> 00:07:37,639
No one wants me.

124
00:07:50,380 --> 00:07:51,781
Jia'er.

125
00:07:52,179 --> 00:07:53,700
Jia'er,

126
00:07:56,839 --> 00:07:58,673
you still have me.

127
00:07:58,680 --> 00:08:00,659
You still have us.

128
00:08:07,242 --> 00:08:12,122
[Episode 25: My Dear Stranger]

129
00:08:30,140 --> 00:08:31,994
Mi Jia,

130
00:08:31,994 --> 00:08:35,519
stay here for the night.

131
00:08:35,519 --> 00:08:39,220
Let's talk about this tomorrow, okay?

132
00:08:45,419 --> 00:08:47,762
I was the one who brought you to Tieyuan.

133
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:54,720
I will take responsibility for this no matter what happens.

134
00:08:57,900 --> 00:08:59,665
Mr. Gao,

135
00:09:01,640 --> 00:09:03,340
can I ask you a favor?

136
00:09:03,340 --> 00:09:07,499
Sure, go ahead. I can do anything for you.

137
00:09:15,939 --> 00:09:19,499
Xiaowen, Gao Yang, you two,

138
00:09:19,499 --> 00:09:22,365
go take a stroll downstairs.

139
00:09:22,365 --> 00:09:23,802
What's wrong?

140
00:09:36,170 --> 00:09:39,020
Mi Jia, go ahead.

141
00:09:39,020 --> 00:09:42,300
I'll do anything for you.

142
00:09:43,579 --> 00:09:45,200
I want to go back to the orphanage.

143
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:46,600
Don't do that.

144
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:48,200
Mi Jia, think about it carefully.

145
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:50,499
I've made my decision.

146
00:09:50,499 --> 00:09:52,329
I have to leave.

147
00:09:53,839 --> 00:09:56,620
Auntie isn't well off

148
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:59,550
and she's still going to...

149
00:10:00,080 --> 00:10:02,120
raise a burden like me.

150
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:07,379
I-I should've left a long time ago.

151
00:10:07,379 --> 00:10:11,240
Mi Jia, no one thinks of you as a burden.

152
00:10:11,240 --> 00:10:12,639
I'll be honest with you.

153
00:10:12,639 --> 00:10:16,259
When we were in Auntie's house, she told me personally that she's reluctant to see you go.

154
00:10:16,259 --> 00:10:19,579
She wants you to stay there forever. Do you understand?

155
00:10:21,819 --> 00:10:23,875
Mi Jia,

156
00:10:23,875 --> 00:10:26,620
you can bet on that.

157
00:10:26,620 --> 00:10:29,659
Don't worry. Nothing is going to happen.

158
00:10:31,440 --> 00:10:37,120
I-If you won't let me go, I-I-I I'll drop out of school.

159
00:10:38,419 --> 00:10:43,340
I-I-I I've been very happy these days.

160
00:10:43,340 --> 00:10:45,097
But...

161
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:49,079
that happiness doesn't belong to me.

162
00:10:52,939 --> 00:10:56,639
Please don't tell Xiaowen yet.

163
00:10:57,639 --> 00:11:00,040
Tell him after I leave.

164
00:11:01,240 --> 00:11:03,359
I'm don't want this to affect him.

165
00:11:05,970 --> 00:11:07,910
Mr. Gao,

166
00:11:09,070 --> 00:11:14,060
you said you'll... you'll do anything for me.

167
00:11:15,900 --> 00:11:18,740
All right. Well,

168
00:11:18,740 --> 00:11:22,419
Mi Jia, just spend the night here.

169
00:11:22,419 --> 00:11:25,460
Tomorrow, I'll take you back to the orphanage.

170
00:11:25,460 --> 00:11:29,710
I'll go get your luggage from Auntie's house. Just stay in the house. Don't go anywhere.

171
00:11:29,710 --> 00:11:31,150
Okay.

172
00:11:33,799 --> 00:11:37,879
What do you think Mi Jia will ask Gao Bin to do?

173
00:11:37,879 --> 00:11:40,100
I'm guessing she wants to go back to the orphanage.

174
00:11:40,100 --> 00:11:42,100
What should we do?

175
00:11:42,100 --> 00:11:44,775
We'll figure something out after Mr. Gao talks to her.

176
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:47,539
Where are you going?

177
00:11:47,539 --> 00:11:49,839
You guys go home first and watch over Mi Jia!

178
00:11:49,840 --> 00:11:51,200
Mr. Gao, what happened to Mi Jia?

179
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:54,240
Don't stop me! Mi Jia won't be here anymore if you keep stopping me!

180
00:11:54,240 --> 00:11:56,070
Be careful!

181
00:12:05,559 --> 00:12:07,799
Be careful!

182
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:14,139
Mi Jia is determined to leave.

183
00:12:14,139 --> 00:12:16,140
I can't convince her.

184
00:12:19,340 --> 00:12:22,739
It's all your fault. Why did you come back?

185
00:12:22,739 --> 00:12:25,020
I just... want to see the child.

186
00:12:25,020 --> 00:12:28,400
Well, look at it now. That child is gone.

187
00:12:28,400 --> 00:12:31,620
I'm telling you, I'll never be done with you if Mi Jia leaves!

188
00:12:31,620 --> 00:12:32,779
I...

189
00:12:32,779 --> 00:12:36,759
Auntie, Mi Jia isn't your real niece.

190
00:12:36,759 --> 00:12:39,138
Do you really want to keep her?

191
00:12:39,138 --> 00:12:41,000
Of course.

192
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:44,479
We spent so much time together. I'm fond of her.

193
00:12:44,479 --> 00:12:46,459
But that's not my fault.

194
00:12:46,459 --> 00:12:49,639
If you can't keep Mi Jia here, I'll blame you.

195
00:12:52,150 --> 00:12:54,260
Judging by Mi Jia's attitude,

196
00:12:54,260 --> 00:12:59,260
you can only convince her to stay if you're her real aunt.

197
00:13:00,419 --> 00:13:02,879
But I'm not.

198
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:07,800
You can be.

199
00:13:48,060 --> 00:13:49,760
Hurry up!

200
00:13:52,360 --> 00:13:53,821
Mi...

201
00:13:54,320 --> 00:13:57,100
Mi... Mi Jia.

202
00:13:57,100 --> 00:13:58,858
I am your...

203
00:13:58,858 --> 00:14:01,900
I am your dad.

204
00:14:03,440 --> 00:14:06,279
I went home and thought about it again.

205
00:14:06,279 --> 00:14:08,000
I remembered it wrong.

206
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:10,879
I didn't have a son.

207
00:14:10,879 --> 00:14:14,330
I had a daughter. I'm your biological father.

208
00:14:14,330 --> 00:14:17,430
Your aunt is your real aunt.

209
00:14:17,430 --> 00:14:20,430
Therefore, we are family.

210
00:14:21,120 --> 00:14:24,879
Come out now. Let's go home.

211
00:14:32,159 --> 00:14:35,479
Jia'er, it's me, Auntie.

212
00:14:35,479 --> 00:14:39,440
Your dad spent more than ten hours on the train yesterday.

213
00:14:39,440 --> 00:14:40,620
He... he got confused.

214
00:14:40,620 --> 00:14:42,500
I got confused.

215
00:14:42,500 --> 00:14:46,620
Don't take his bullshit to heart. You belong in our family.

216
00:14:48,760 --> 00:14:50,707
Why don't I hear anything?

217
00:14:55,960 --> 00:14:57,279
Oh, no! Mi Jia ran away!

218
00:14:57,279 --> 00:14:58,936
Hurry up!

219
00:15:03,770 --> 00:15:05,888
How can she run away like this?

220
00:15:12,360 --> 00:15:15,940
She... She really ran away?

221
00:15:15,940 --> 00:15:18,940
She's a girl. She didn't bring any money.

222
00:15:18,940 --> 00:15:23,900
If she got lost and... something happens to her, what should we do?

223
00:15:27,260 --> 00:15:28,150
Auntie!

224
00:15:28,150 --> 00:15:31,450
Sister! Don't be anxious.

225
00:15:31,450 --> 00:15:32,999
Don't be anxious.

226
00:15:32,999 --> 00:15:34,279
The train station!

227
00:15:34,279 --> 00:15:35,740
Okay.

228
00:15:35,740 --> 00:15:37,260
Daqiang, take care of Auntie.

229
00:15:37,260 --> 00:15:39,260
Don't worry, Auntie. We'll definitely bring Mi Jia home.

230
00:15:39,260 --> 00:15:40,620
Mr. Gao!

231
00:15:40,620 --> 00:15:43,202
Tell me when you find her!

232
00:15:43,202 --> 00:15:44,842
[Tie Yuan Station]

233
00:15:48,459 --> 00:15:49,860
I'm sorry.

234
00:15:49,860 --> 00:15:54,506
Mi Jia!

235
00:15:54,506 --> 00:15:56,260
Hi, have you seen a girl

236
00:15:56,260 --> 00:15:58,399
with a pony tail about this tall?

237
00:15:58,399 --> 00:15:59,710
Mi Jia!

238
00:15:59,710 --> 00:16:02,800
Have you seen a girl with a pony tail and two bangs on her forehead?

239
00:16:02,800 --> 00:16:04,700
Mi Jia!

240
00:16:04,700 --> 00:16:07,120
A 17 or 18-year-old girl bout this tall.

241
00:16:07,120 --> 00:16:11,020
Hello, have you seen a 17 or 18-year-old girl about this tall?

242
00:16:11,020 --> 00:16:14,900
- Hello, have you seen a 17 or 18-year-old girl? She's about this tall.
- Mi Jia!

243
00:16:14,900 --> 00:16:16,306
Mi Jia!

244
00:16:16,306 --> 00:16:17,740
Mi Jia!

245
00:16:17,740 --> 00:16:18,640
Thank you.

246
00:16:18,640 --> 00:16:20,160
Mi Jia!

247
00:16:20,160 --> 00:16:22,590
What do you want?

248
00:16:27,220 --> 00:16:28,884
Mi Jia!

249
00:16:30,020 --> 00:16:31,440
- Mi Jia!
- Mi Jia!

250
00:16:31,440 --> 00:16:34,459
Mr. Gao, we've looked through so many compartments.

251
00:16:34,459 --> 00:16:37,759
Do you think she didn't get on this train?

252
00:16:38,419 --> 00:16:40,138
That's not right.

253
00:16:40,138 --> 00:16:41,800
This is the only train.

254
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:45,510
If Mi Jia didn't get on this train, how will she go back to the orphanage?

255
00:16:45,510 --> 00:16:47,559
The coach.

256
00:16:47,559 --> 00:16:48,819
That's right!

257
00:16:48,819 --> 00:16:50,639
You two keep looking. I'll go to the coach station.

258
00:16:50,639 --> 00:16:52,519
Call me if you find her.

259
00:16:52,519 --> 00:16:55,079
- Let's go.
- Mi Jia!

260
00:17:36,380 --> 00:17:38,300
- Mi Jia!
- Mi Jia!

261
00:17:38,300 --> 00:17:39,359
Mi Jia!

262
00:17:39,359 --> 00:17:40,620
What are you here for?

263
00:17:40,620 --> 00:17:42,219
I'm sorry. We're looking for someone.

264
00:17:42,219 --> 00:17:43,559
The train is about to leave. Get off the train soon.

265
00:17:43,559 --> 00:17:45,060
I know. Please help us out.

266
00:17:45,060 --> 00:17:47,680
Our sister went missing. The family is very worried.

267
00:17:47,680 --> 00:17:49,179
All right, then. Make it quick. Five more minutes.

268
00:17:49,179 --> 00:17:50,419
- Thank you.
- Thank you, Sir.

269
00:17:50,419 --> 00:17:52,251
Mi Jia!

270
00:18:00,442 --> 00:18:02,762
[Tie Yuan Long Distance Bus Station]

271
00:18:07,520 --> 00:18:09,310
Mr. Gao?

272
00:18:10,540 --> 00:18:12,000
Dawei.

273
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:12,919
- Beer, beverages...
- Mi Jia!

274
00:18:12,919 --> 00:18:15,060
- Mi Jia!
- ...mineral water, peanuts...

275
00:18:15,060 --> 00:18:17,081
- Mi Jia!
- Tea.

276
00:18:17,081 --> 00:18:18,340
Mi Jia!

277
00:18:18,340 --> 00:18:19,884
What's wrong?

278
00:18:21,920 --> 00:18:24,000
I know where Mi Jia is.

279
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:25,910
Excuse me, where is the dining compartment?

280
00:18:25,910 --> 00:18:27,680
- Over there.
- Thank you.

281
00:18:27,680 --> 00:18:29,323
What do you mean?

282
00:18:52,190 --> 00:18:55,920
Just... just leave me alone.

283
00:18:55,920 --> 00:18:58,287
I want to go back to the orphanage.

284
00:18:58,287 --> 00:19:01,079
Mi Jia, come home with us.

285
00:19:01,979 --> 00:19:03,659
I'm not going.

286
00:19:03,659 --> 00:19:06,859
That's not my home.

287
00:19:06,859 --> 00:19:08,580
W-Why should I go back?

288
00:19:08,580 --> 00:19:10,480
How is it not your home?

289
00:19:10,480 --> 00:19:12,699
You and Auntie spent so much time together.

290
00:19:12,699 --> 00:19:14,300
Auntie is so nice to you.

291
00:19:14,300 --> 00:19:17,519
What would she do if you leave?

292
00:19:18,759 --> 00:19:21,720
S-Stop trying to convince me.

293
00:19:21,720 --> 00:19:23,820
I want to go back to the orphanage.

294
00:19:34,559 --> 00:19:39,140
Jia, I know what you're thinking.

295
00:19:40,160 --> 00:19:42,029
You think

296
00:19:42,720 --> 00:19:45,670
since you're not related to Auntie

297
00:19:46,040 --> 00:19:48,580
you're not family

298
00:19:48,580 --> 00:19:50,939
and you don't want to trouble her.

299
00:19:50,939 --> 00:19:55,359
But... is the most important thing between family

300
00:19:55,730 --> 00:19:57,780
their blood ties?

301
00:20:00,820 --> 00:20:02,100
Look,

302
00:20:02,100 --> 00:20:05,140
Gao Yang and I are not related.

303
00:20:05,140 --> 00:20:08,679
But I already think of Mr. Gao

304
00:20:08,679 --> 00:20:10,759
and him as family.

305
00:20:10,759 --> 00:20:12,485
That's right.

306
00:20:12,485 --> 00:20:15,065
We're family. The Brethren of Tieyuan.

307
00:20:18,219 --> 00:20:20,409
It's the same for us.

308
00:20:20,409 --> 00:20:24,500
Although we're not related,

309
00:20:24,500 --> 00:20:29,540
I've always treated you like my own sister.

310
00:20:32,160 --> 00:20:37,599
I can tell that Auntie really wants to keep you here.

311
00:20:39,650 --> 00:20:41,979
Give her a chance.

312
00:20:53,380 --> 00:20:54,640
How did it go?

313
00:20:54,640 --> 00:20:57,579
Mr. Gao, I've asked around the train station. No one saw Mi Jia.

314
00:20:57,579 --> 00:21:01,320
But I already told them if they see her, they'll give you a call.

315
00:21:01,320 --> 00:21:02,736
Okay.

316
00:21:04,760 --> 00:21:06,079
Dawei,

317
00:21:06,079 --> 00:21:07,699
you spent all your time helping me today.

318
00:21:07,699 --> 00:21:09,800
Did I delay your deliveries?

319
00:21:09,800 --> 00:21:12,160
I took the day off.

320
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:14,900
They must've deducted your pay.

321
00:21:14,900 --> 00:21:17,739
I'll compensate you.

322
00:21:17,739 --> 00:21:21,305
Mr. Gao, don't be such a stranger. You're my teacher.

323
00:21:21,305 --> 00:21:23,599
I should help you.

324
00:21:26,459 --> 00:21:29,000
I'm not a good teacher.

325
00:21:29,880 --> 00:21:31,680
I didn't do a good job with the soccer team.

326
00:21:31,680 --> 00:21:33,839
The track and field team fired me too.

327
00:21:33,839 --> 00:21:36,540
I thought I found Mi Jia's family,

328
00:21:36,540 --> 00:21:38,794
but I ended up making a mistake.

329
00:21:40,340 --> 00:21:45,119
Mr. Gao, you are a good teacher.

330
00:21:52,559 --> 00:21:54,237
Hello?

331
00:21:54,237 --> 00:21:57,659
Gao Yang, you found Mi Jia?

332
00:21:57,659 --> 00:22:00,660
That's great! Thank God!

333
00:22:01,340 --> 00:22:06,100
All right, you guys are in charge of bringing Mi Jia back home safely.

334
00:22:06,100 --> 00:22:07,738
I...

335
00:22:09,799 --> 00:22:12,519
I'll be there soon!

336
00:22:12,519 --> 00:22:15,180
Sure. I'll see you later.

337
00:22:16,920 --> 00:22:18,365
Mr. Gao,

338
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:20,644
I'll take you there.

339
00:22:23,179 --> 00:22:24,659
Okay, thank you.

340
00:22:24,659 --> 00:22:26,115
Let's go.

341
00:22:30,160 --> 00:22:35,299
Jia'er! Jia'er, you really scared me!

342
00:22:35,299 --> 00:22:38,200
Auntie, I was wrong.

343
00:22:38,200 --> 00:22:42,420
What are you talking about? You will always be my good girl.

344
00:22:42,420 --> 00:22:47,480
But Auntie, I'm not related to you.

345
00:22:47,480 --> 00:22:53,579
I was sure you belonged to our family since the first day I met you.

346
00:22:53,579 --> 00:22:56,179
It doesn't matter if we're related.

347
00:22:56,179 --> 00:22:59,140
You're family to me.

348
00:23:01,300 --> 00:23:02,359
Auntie.

349
00:23:02,359 --> 00:23:05,400
Mi Jia, don't cry.

350
00:23:05,400 --> 00:23:09,359
Don't leave anymore, okay? I was so worried.

351
00:23:09,359 --> 00:23:10,440
Don't cry.

352
00:23:10,440 --> 00:23:13,040
I don't want to trouble you.

353
00:23:18,780 --> 00:23:20,979
Don't cry.

354
00:23:24,060 --> 00:23:25,959
Mi Jia is already home.

355
00:23:25,959 --> 00:23:29,179
Wait for you? It'll be too late.

356
00:23:29,179 --> 00:23:32,319
Don't come over. We're leaving now.

357
00:23:32,319 --> 00:23:34,419
That's it. I'm hanging up.

358
00:23:39,160 --> 00:23:40,838
What's wrong?

359
00:23:40,838 --> 00:23:42,672
Nothing.

360
00:23:42,672 --> 00:23:45,359
I just think destiny is pretty strange.

361
00:23:45,359 --> 00:23:47,910
Do you think there's a special connection between us?

362
00:23:49,519 --> 00:23:53,240
You just said it yourself on the train. We are family.

363
00:23:53,970 --> 00:23:55,688
Call me Brother.

364
00:23:55,688 --> 00:23:59,019
Right here. Harder.

365
00:23:59,019 --> 00:24:00,905
That feels good.

366
00:24:00,905 --> 00:24:03,499
We just asked you to find someone and you sprained your lower back.

367
00:24:03,499 --> 00:24:05,513
What else can you do?

368
00:24:05,513 --> 00:24:08,840
I was in a rush. I'm afraid Mi Jia would run away.

369
00:24:09,499 --> 00:24:11,940
Mr. Gao, where's your bike?

370
00:24:11,940 --> 00:24:13,039
That bike...

371
00:24:13,039 --> 00:24:15,580
I fell and I left the bike at the repair shop.

372
00:24:15,580 --> 00:24:17,699
Which repair shop? I'll go get it back.

373
00:24:17,699 --> 00:24:20,119
No, that's okay. It probably can't be fixed.

374
00:24:20,119 --> 00:24:22,187
I'm planning to buy a new one.

375
00:24:23,380 --> 00:24:24,440
What are you doing?

376
00:24:24,440 --> 00:24:27,868
Are you rich? That's another expense, you know?

377
00:24:29,499 --> 00:24:33,500
Don't bring up money all the time. That's so vulgar.

378
00:24:33,500 --> 00:24:36,979
It's good enough that Mi Jia and Auntie will live happily ever after.

379
00:24:36,979 --> 00:24:41,299
We can always earn more money. I'll go to work tomorrow.

380
00:24:41,299 --> 00:24:45,319
Mr. Gao, your lower back... You should rest at home for a few days.

381
00:24:45,319 --> 00:24:47,759
No, that's alright. I already took a few days off.

382
00:24:47,759 --> 00:24:51,619
If I keep that up, the Vice Principal will fire me.

383
00:24:51,619 --> 00:24:53,599
Even so, don't fight with him.

384
00:24:53,599 --> 00:24:55,079
I won't fight with him for sure.

385
00:24:55,079 --> 00:24:57,680
What do you want? You won't let me be the coach!

386
00:24:57,680 --> 00:24:59,759
Am I not good enough to be the assistant either?

387
00:24:59,759 --> 00:25:04,619
After all, I've been teaching for over 20 years. Why can't I assist Xiao Li?

388
00:25:04,619 --> 00:25:06,860
Gao Bin, get it through to your head.

389
00:25:06,860 --> 00:25:08,659
You're the one who's asking me for a favor!

390
00:25:08,659 --> 00:25:09,739
What kind of attitude is that?

391
00:25:09,739 --> 00:25:12,039
What's wrong with my attitude? Aren't I apologizing to you now?

392
00:25:12,039 --> 00:25:13,079
How are you apologizing?

393
00:25:13,079 --> 00:25:15,920
- I'm sorry!
- Sorry won't cut it!

394
00:25:15,920 --> 00:25:18,519
Go back to class! Go, go, go!

395
00:25:18,519 --> 00:25:21,039
What the hell is this?

396
00:25:44,363 --> 00:25:46,143
What... what are you doing?

397
00:25:47,079 --> 00:25:48,613
Vice Principal,

398
00:25:49,580 --> 00:25:53,820
please let me be the assistant coach of the track and field team.

399
00:25:54,380 --> 00:25:56,757
This is very important to me.

400
00:25:56,757 --> 00:25:59,580
Why can't I tell it's important to you?

401
00:26:00,569 --> 00:26:02,819
I know I have a lot of shortcomings.

402
00:26:02,819 --> 00:26:06,599
I also have a lofty attitude and I'm careless

403
00:26:06,599 --> 00:26:10,800
Gao Yang looks down upon me.

404
00:26:10,800 --> 00:26:14,780
When I'm not doing well at work, I think it's someone else's fault.

405
00:26:14,780 --> 00:26:16,979
Actually, these are all my responsibility.

406
00:26:16,979 --> 00:26:20,679
But it's not the same after Xiaowen came. Everything changed.

407
00:26:20,679 --> 00:26:22,919
When I look at that boy,

408
00:26:26,170 --> 00:26:29,219
I really don't think I'm a qualified adult.

409
00:26:29,820 --> 00:26:31,687
He's more

410
00:26:32,380 --> 00:26:36,260
calm, composed, and more responsible than I am.

411
00:26:37,580 --> 00:26:43,880
As the assistant, I just want to start from the beginning and improve the scores of Xiaowen and the other kids.

412
00:26:45,900 --> 00:26:48,380
Actually, being the coach or not

413
00:26:49,170 --> 00:26:50,787
is not important.

414
00:26:52,780 --> 00:26:57,499
Well, that's all I want to say.

415
00:26:58,580 --> 00:27:00,228
I'm sorry.

416
00:27:09,459 --> 00:27:11,109
Wait a minute.

417
00:27:19,060 --> 00:27:23,600
Bin, since you put it that way,

418
00:27:24,380 --> 00:27:27,480
fine. I approve.

419
00:27:28,460 --> 00:27:30,259
But you have to remember one thing.

420
00:27:30,259 --> 00:27:32,900
Do not affect the normal teaching.

421
00:27:32,900 --> 00:27:33,840
I understand.

422
00:27:33,840 --> 00:27:36,119
You have to understand something else too.

423
00:27:36,119 --> 00:27:38,759
I never purposely made things difficult for you.

424
00:27:38,759 --> 00:27:42,659
It's a big school and I'm responsible for so many things.

425
00:27:42,659 --> 00:27:43,620
I understand.

426
00:27:43,620 --> 00:27:46,359
All right, you don't have to understand anything else.

427
00:27:46,359 --> 00:27:48,359
Good luck. Do your best.

428
00:27:48,359 --> 00:27:51,434
Try to obtain the title of "Outstanding Teacher" next year.

429
00:27:53,210 --> 00:27:55,024
Old Fu,

430
00:27:55,024 --> 00:27:56,560
thank you.

431
00:27:57,210 --> 00:27:58,838
Thank you.

432
00:28:06,519 --> 00:28:07,967
Come on.

433
00:28:08,690 --> 00:28:12,080
Don't worry, starting tomorrow, I'll coach the team with Li.

434
00:28:12,080 --> 00:28:12,839
It's fine now.

435
00:28:12,839 --> 00:28:14,459
That's great, Mr. Gao.

436
00:28:14,459 --> 00:28:15,599
Congratulations.

437
00:28:15,599 --> 00:28:18,860
You finally pulled through and got promoted to assistant.

438
00:28:18,860 --> 00:28:20,839
Swallow that annoying comment.

439
00:28:20,839 --> 00:28:24,583
I'm happy if I can coach the team. I just have to try harder slowly, right?
- Yes.

440
00:28:24,583 --> 00:28:28,180
That's a commendable spirit. What's that idiom again?

441
00:28:28,180 --> 00:28:30,034
Adapt to the situation.

442
00:28:30,034 --> 00:28:31,881
Dong Dawei?

443
00:28:33,620 --> 00:28:36,960
Mr. Gao, I fixed the bike for you.

444
00:28:45,100 --> 00:28:47,960
Just throw my old, shabby bike away.

445
00:28:47,960 --> 00:28:49,839
You didn't have to go through the trouble.

446
00:28:49,839 --> 00:28:53,500
I just fixed it conveniently. My family is in that trade.

447
00:28:56,119 --> 00:29:00,680
Dawei, have you really decided not to repeat school?

448
00:29:04,030 --> 00:29:05,979
But don't worry, Mr. Gao.

449
00:29:05,979 --> 00:29:10,340
Even if I don't repeat school, I won't give up on myself.

450
00:29:10,340 --> 00:29:12,320
I'm already an adult now.

451
00:29:12,920 --> 00:29:16,180
College life doesn't suit me.

452
00:29:17,179 --> 00:29:21,199
However, I do cherish the memories.

453
00:29:25,730 --> 00:29:27,037
Wait right here.

454
00:29:27,037 --> 00:29:29,400
- Mr. Gao, where are you going?
- Wait here.

455
00:29:55,480 --> 00:29:56,850
Dawei,

456
00:29:58,440 --> 00:29:59,983
take this.

457
00:30:00,400 --> 00:30:02,075
Keep it as a memento.

458
00:30:11,519 --> 00:30:13,539
Hurry up, class is about to start.

459
00:30:15,119 --> 00:30:16,661
Gao Yang.

460
00:30:18,100 --> 00:30:19,529
Dong.

461
00:30:20,960 --> 00:30:23,020
- Why? I'm not welcomed here?
- No, no.

462
00:30:23,020 --> 00:30:24,759
Welcome, welcome.

463
00:30:24,759 --> 00:30:26,460
A warm welcome to you.

464
00:30:26,460 --> 00:30:29,086
I'm just here to say goodbye. What are you so nervous for?

465
00:30:31,240 --> 00:30:33,359
Where's Xiaowen? I want to tell him as well.

466
00:30:33,359 --> 00:30:35,000
Well, he's in training.

467
00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:36,480
Just tell me about it.

468
00:30:36,480 --> 00:30:38,128
I'm his brother now.

469
00:30:39,440 --> 00:30:41,400
Well, learn something from him.

470
00:30:41,400 --> 00:30:44,599
You're not even good enough to be a driver now. I'm leaving.

471
00:30:44,599 --> 00:30:46,332
Go now.

472
00:30:46,332 --> 00:30:48,003
Wait, Brother Dong.

473
00:30:48,799 --> 00:30:52,576
Well, I wish you smooth sailing all the way.

474
00:30:52,576 --> 00:30:53,998
I mean it.

475
00:30:55,759 --> 00:30:57,131
I'm leaving.

476
00:31:02,859 --> 00:31:04,100
You...

477
00:31:04,100 --> 00:31:05,609
Why are you here?

478
00:31:06,440 --> 00:31:09,399
I... I brought Mr. Gao's bike back to him.

479
00:31:09,399 --> 00:31:11,760
How have you been lately?

480
00:31:13,680 --> 00:31:15,679
I... I'm all right.

481
00:31:17,680 --> 00:31:19,214
Wanwan,

482
00:31:21,559 --> 00:31:23,522
let's have dinner together after school.

483
00:31:27,519 --> 00:31:29,919
Are... are you coming or not?

484
00:31:33,079 --> 00:31:35,250
I don't want kabobs.

485
00:31:35,250 --> 00:31:36,440
Okay.

486
00:31:39,759 --> 00:31:42,559
There's a member of our team today.

487
00:31:42,559 --> 00:31:45,560
You should all be very familiar with this team member.

488
00:31:45,560 --> 00:31:48,119
Let's welcome Mr. Gao back to the team!

489
00:31:52,799 --> 00:31:56,560
From now on, I will help Mr. Li with your training.

490
00:31:56,560 --> 00:31:57,920
It's pretty windy today.

491
00:31:57,920 --> 00:31:59,480
Be careful, Everyone.

492
00:31:59,480 --> 00:32:01,279
If anyone has a cramp or needs to stretch,

493
00:32:01,279 --> 00:32:02,519
let me know at any time.

494
00:32:02,519 --> 00:32:05,140
We won't let anyone get hurt.

495
00:32:05,140 --> 00:32:06,502
Applaud!

496
00:32:10,720 --> 00:32:12,359
Mr. Li, shall we...

497
00:32:12,359 --> 00:32:13,119
Begin?

498
00:32:13,119 --> 00:32:14,263
Okay, okay.

499
00:32:16,739 --> 00:32:18,260
Start running.

500
00:32:34,830 --> 00:32:38,210
[Tian Yuan High School]

501
00:32:41,739 --> 00:32:44,260
This is Zhao Wenzhe, he has quite an explosive force.

502
00:32:44,260 --> 00:32:48,199
His techniques are suitable for 100m or 200m dashes.

503
00:32:48,199 --> 00:32:49,800
Come on, keep up!

504
00:32:49,800 --> 00:32:51,799
Ye Xiaowen has good stamina.

505
00:32:51,799 --> 00:32:54,028
These two made a big improvement.

506
00:32:54,028 --> 00:32:57,360
He's more suitable for long-distance races.

507
00:33:08,140 --> 00:33:10,539
Dad, have a piece of apple.

508
00:33:13,419 --> 00:33:16,599
Doudou, you should have one too. Replenish your vitamin C.

509
00:33:21,699 --> 00:33:23,759
Jia'er, come on.

510
00:33:23,759 --> 00:33:26,399
Look, I just made this for you.

511
00:33:26,399 --> 00:33:27,600
Does it look nice?

512
00:33:27,600 --> 00:33:28,930
Okay.

513
00:33:32,480 --> 00:33:33,959
It's perfect.

514
00:33:34,599 --> 00:33:36,284
You look so pretty.

515
00:33:38,039 --> 00:33:41,300
See, I told you our child has artistic talents.

516
00:33:41,300 --> 00:33:42,620
He passed the exam on the first try.

517
00:33:42,620 --> 00:33:44,440
Young people should chase their dreams.

518
00:33:44,440 --> 00:33:46,759
He got his musical gene from me.

519
00:33:46,759 --> 00:33:48,240
He got his artistic talents from me.

520
00:33:48,240 --> 00:33:49,580
- He got it from me.
- He got it from me.

521
00:33:49,580 --> 00:33:51,100
- He really got it from me.
- He got it from me.

522
00:33:51,100 --> 00:33:52,319
- He... he...
- He got it from me!

523
00:33:52,319 --> 00:33:53,980
Yes, he got it from you.

524
00:33:53,980 --> 00:33:55,300
Beibei, Mi Jia!

525
00:33:55,300 --> 00:33:57,480
Over here! What happened?

526
00:33:57,480 --> 00:33:59,719
- My article is published!
- Let me see it. See?

527
00:33:59,719 --> 00:34:02,319
Dreams of the Night.

528
00:34:02,319 --> 00:34:04,700
Meng, that's wonderful!

529
00:34:04,700 --> 00:34:08,150
[Dreams of the Night]

530
00:34:09,599 --> 00:34:11,679
Come on, try my cooking.

531
00:34:11,679 --> 00:34:12,820
I've practiced for a long time.

532
00:34:12,820 --> 00:34:14,380
None of them broke.

533
00:34:14,380 --> 00:34:15,939
I'm so proud of you.

534
00:34:16,679 --> 00:34:19,200
- Xiaowen, try one.
- Okay.

535
00:34:20,419 --> 00:34:21,946
What do you think?

536
00:34:23,000 --> 00:34:25,739
I have to say, you've improved.

537
00:34:26,440 --> 00:34:28,293
- Yummy.
- Not bad.

538
00:34:29,000 --> 00:34:30,468
Let's eat in a minute.

539
00:34:32,216 --> 00:34:34,297
It's the Mid-Autumn Festival.

540
00:34:34,297 --> 00:34:35,860
I have a few words to say.

541
00:34:35,860 --> 00:34:41,039
First of all, I wish for Xiaowen to win first place in the national competition

542
00:34:41,039 --> 00:34:42,579
and bring honor to Tieyuan.

543
00:34:42,579 --> 00:34:44,260
Thank you, Mr. Gao.

544
00:34:44,260 --> 00:34:46,059
I wish Gao Yang...

545
00:34:48,080 --> 00:34:50,300
I wish Gao Yang can pass the college entrance exam.

546
00:34:50,300 --> 00:34:53,239
That's not good enough. I have to go to a good college.

547
00:34:53,239 --> 00:34:54,639
It's good enough that you're accepted to any college.

548
00:34:54,639 --> 00:34:57,060
Be realistic.

549
00:34:57,060 --> 00:34:59,139
I... I wish Mr. Gao...

550
00:34:59,139 --> 00:35:01,240
- I wish everything goes well with your work.
- Thank you.

551
00:35:01,240 --> 00:35:02,939
Get the "Outstanding Teacher" title soon!

552
00:35:02,939 --> 00:35:04,222
Get a raise.

553
00:35:05,079 --> 00:35:08,340
- Get a raise.
- That's too mundane.

554
00:35:08,340 --> 00:35:10,332
Xiaowen, say something not mundane.

555
00:35:12,639 --> 00:35:18,460
I wish we can spend next year's Mid-Autumn Festival together as well.

556
00:35:18,460 --> 00:35:22,400
I wish we can spend every Mid-Autumn Festival together in the future.

557
00:35:23,539 --> 00:35:26,213
- Happy Mid-Autumn Festival!
- Happy Mid-Autumn Festival!

558
00:35:29,579 --> 00:35:33,220
Let's give Third Uncle a call so he can be happy too.

559
00:35:44,419 --> 00:35:47,700
Hello? Uncle, I'm Bin.

560
00:35:47,700 --> 00:35:49,333
Wait a minute.

561
00:35:51,039 --> 00:35:54,159
Happy Mid-Autumn Festival!

562
00:35:54,159 --> 00:35:55,440
Back at you.

563
00:35:55,440 --> 00:35:58,000
Hello, Bin. Hello, Xiaowen.

564
00:35:58,000 --> 00:36:00,679
Great Uncle, why didn't you greet me?

565
00:36:00,679 --> 00:36:02,532
I'm Gao Yang.

566
00:36:02,532 --> 00:36:04,939
I've forgotten about you.

567
00:36:04,939 --> 00:36:07,619
Wait, Great Uncle, you're so biased.

568
00:36:08,400 --> 00:36:10,440
I'm just kidding.

569
00:36:10,440 --> 00:36:11,840
Hello, Gao Yang.

570
00:36:11,840 --> 00:36:13,679
I have good news for you.

571
00:36:13,679 --> 00:36:15,000
Tiger has a wife now.

572
00:36:15,000 --> 00:36:16,539
They had a few puppies.

573
00:36:16,539 --> 00:36:19,660
- Do you want one?
- No, no, that's not necessary.

574
00:36:19,679 --> 00:36:21,378
Thank you, Great Uncle.

575
00:36:22,000 --> 00:36:24,060
All right, Uncle. Go celebrate the holiday.

576
00:36:24,060 --> 00:36:25,920
We'll go visit you soon.

577
00:36:25,920 --> 00:36:26,960
That's all right.

578
00:36:26,960 --> 00:36:30,219
I'll go to Tieyuan to visit you in a few days.

579
00:36:32,440 --> 00:36:34,939
Third Uncle, you're coming to Tieyuan?

580
00:36:34,939 --> 00:36:37,580
- What for?
- Isn't Anna back today?

581
00:36:37,580 --> 00:36:39,719
She didn't go visit Gao Yang?

582
00:36:44,280 --> 00:36:46,620
Forget I said that.

583
00:36:46,620 --> 00:36:49,020
If there's nothing else, I'll hang up.

584
00:36:57,360 --> 00:36:58,942
My mom is back?

585
00:37:28,802 --> 00:37:34,750
♫ I know the direction of dawn ♫

586
00:37:34,750 --> 00:37:42,115
♫ It's right in front of me ♫

587
00:37:42,115 --> 00:37:48,105
♫ Starlight shines along the way ♫

588
00:37:48,105 --> 00:37:54,145
♫ Accompanying me on my adventure ♫

589
00:37:54,145 --> 00:38:00,797
♫ I don't fear how rough the journey might be ♫

590
00:38:00,797 --> 00:38:04,937
♫ Maybe ♫

591
00:38:04,937 --> 00:38:10,324
♫ Go ♫

592
00:38:10,350 --> 00:38:13,772
♫ Set sail for your dreams ♫

593
00:38:13,772 --> 00:38:17,067
♫ Don't leave any regret in your youth ♫

594
00:38:17,067 --> 00:38:23,827
♫ Even if it hurts all over ♫

595
00:38:23,835 --> 00:38:27,038
♫ Find the answer through the crazies path ♫

596
00:38:27,038 --> 00:38:31,250
♫ Break the storm with the bravest heart ♫

597
00:38:31,250 --> 00:38:35,070
♫ I'll flap my wings to fly to the future ♫

598
00:38:35,070 --> 00:38:43,030
♫ And go straight forward without any sorrow ♫
